                    his tablet” (top) and “In the name of the father, Son and Holy Spirit” (on
                    tablet)</q></desc></decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#80r" facs="081">Fol. 80r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1067LastSupper">The Last Supper</ref> with caption <q>“Maundy
                    Thursday.”</q></desc></decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#88v" facs="090">Fol. 88v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref>, raising <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1386Adam">Adam</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3926Eve">Eve</persName>. Two evil men below
                  (showing one eye). “How he rose from the dead on the third day,” “with Adam”
                  (right), and “with Eve” (left)</desc></decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#101r" facs="102">Fol. 101r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and
                  the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/> with captions <q>“Saint George,” “Burutawit,” and
                    “Dragon.”</q></desc></decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#111r" facs="112">Fol. 111r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref>, accompanied by five angels
                  with captions <q>“Saint Michael” (top left), “Saint Gabriel” (top
                  right)</q></desc></decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#120r" facs="121">Fol. 120r</locus><desc>Luke,
                  the vangelist <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1013EvaPortrait">Evangelist Portrait</ref> with captions
                    <q>“Saint Michael” (top left), “Saint Gabriel” (top right)</q></desc></decoNote>
              <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d11"> Decorative designs: <locus target="#1r" facs="002">fols. 1r, </locus> (ḥaräg); <locus target="#18r #23v #51r #62r #64v #72r #87v #96v #105r #109v #118v #120v" facs="019 025 052 063 066 073 089 098 106 111 120 122">18r, 23v, 51r, 62r, 64v, 72r, 87v, 96v, 105r, 109v, 118v, 120v, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                  <locus target="#54v #79r #87v" facs="056 080 089">54v, 79r, 87v, </locus> (a line of full stops and a
                line of alternating red and black dots); <locus target="#92r #96v #105r" facs="093 098 106">92r, 96v, 105r</locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots) </decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
            <additions>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="e1">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus> blank </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="a1">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#55v" facs="057">Fol. 55v</locus> mentions <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6876Matewos">Mātewos X</persName> and
                      <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7830Petros">Ṗeṭros IV</persName>
                  </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e2">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#1 #13 #27 #42 #59 #79 #89 #100 #110 #119" facs="002 014 028 043 060 080 090101 111 120">Fols. 1, 13, 27, 42, 59, 79, 89, 100, 110, 119</locus> brown yarn is sewn into the
                    fore edge to indicate location of illuminations </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e3">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#46" facs="047">Fol. 46</locus> white thread is sewn into the fore edge to mark
                    content </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e4">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#72" facs="073">Fol. 72</locus> red yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark
                    content </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e5">
                  <desc> marginal notation throughout, some of which might be overlooked text
                  </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e6">
                  <desc> Numbered quires: quires 2–16 </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="a">
                  <desc> Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#4r #20v #52r #60v" facs="005 022 062">folss. 4r, 20v, 52r, 60v, </locus> etc.); words of text are
                    written in the upper margin with a symbol ( ) marking the location where the
                    text is to be inserted (<locus target="#35r" facs="036"> f. 35, col. 2, line
                      9</locus>), and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#60v" facs="062"> f. 60v, col. 2, line 9</locus><locus target="#86r" facs="087"> f. 86r, col. 1, line 8</locus><locus target="#106v" facs="108"> f.
                      106v, col. 2, line 10</locus>); text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#49v #98r" facs="051 099">49v, 98r</locus>) </desc>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
            <bindingDesc>
              <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 255 x 200 x 77 mm, four Coptic chain stitches
                  attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood,
                  covered with tooled leather, headband and tailband.</decoNote>
                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                  <material key="parchment"/>
                  <material key="wood"/>
                  <material key="leather"/>
                </decoNote>
              </binding>
            </bindingDesc>
          </physDesc>
